# b00t direnv configuration
# This file demonstrates the b00t pattern: direnv → .envrc → dotenv → .env
#
# Setup:
#   1. Copy this file: cp .envrc.example .envrc
#   2. Copy .env.example: cp .env.example .env
#   3. Edit .env with your actual API keys
#   4. Enable direnv: direnv allow
#
# The b00t pattern:
#   - direnv automatically loads .envrc when entering directory
#   - .envrc calls dotenv to load environment variables from .env
#   - .env contains actual API keys (gitignored for security)
#   - Datums in ~/.dotfiles/_b00t_/ specify WHICH env vars are required
#   - Python code validates required vars exist via b00t datum system

# Load project .env file (contains API keys)
dotenv

# Optionally load home directory .env for global keys
# dotenv ~/.env

# Optionally load additional environment-specific configs
# dotenv .env.local
# dotenv .env.development

# You can also set project-specific variables here
# export PROJECT_NAME="b00t-j0b-py"
# export LOG_LEVEL="INFO"

# Layout python - ensures direnv works with Python virtual environments
# Uncomment if using a venv:
# layout python python3.12
